## Setup

### Prerequisites
- GCP account with billing enabled
- `gcloud` CLI installed and authenticated
- Python 3.11+
- AviationStack free API key

### Deploy

```bash
git clone https://github.com/sarthak2504/skypulse-travel-intelligence.git
cd skypulse-travel-intelligence

gcloud auth login
gcloud config set project YOUR_PROJECT_ID

# Enable APIs
gcloud services enable pubsub.googleapis.com storage.googleapis.com \
  cloudfunctions.googleapis.com cloudscheduler.googleapis.com \
  iam.googleapis.com cloudbuild.googleapis.com run.googleapis.com \
  dataflow.googleapis.com bigquery.googleapis.com dataproc.googleapis.com

# Deploy Function B (price ticker)
cd functions/function_b
pip install -r requirements.txt
gcloud functions deploy function-b-price-ticker --gen2 --runtime=python311 \
  --region=us-east1 --source=. --entry-point=run --trigger-http \
  --memory=256MB --timeout=60s

# Deploy Dataflow pipeline
cd ../../dataflow
python -m venv venv --system-site-packages
venv/Scripts/activate  # Windows
pip install apache-beam[gcp]==2.74.0
python pipeline.py

# Run Spark batch job
gsutil cp spark/batch_job.py gs://YOUR_BUCKET/spark/batch_job.py
gcloud dataproc batches submit pyspark gs://YOUR_BUCKET/spark/batch_job.py \
  --region=us-central1 --deps-bucket=gs://YOUR_BUCKET
```

Full setup documented in `commands.md`.

